,Recommended,305920,12291077,"Posted: 29 September, 2014",all,MaybeJustice,"Another Perspective is quite an interesting game to say the least. There isn't really a story. The game more or less tries teach the player about a way of thinking, which explains the title. ""So... The title is a spoiler?"" you'd might ask. ""Exactly."" would be my reply, but the game tells it in quite an intriguing way,  a way I personally didn't see coming. It takes, the whole there's someone else who sais and thinks diffirent thing, what you've seen in the trailers and takes it few steps further. This, in turn, gives the story a little more weight to it, and, in my books, makes it a little bit better. The game really tries to make you think, but after a while it will be a little more brunt with its message, and you will notice that. That's quite the shame though, because at one point it really was making me ponder and this just made me lose the immersion it created.Now for the mechanics and design.Lets start with the art design:The art design is pretty good. The levels look boring, just brown and grey brown. The character though, that's what I really liked. The drawing style was just a breath a fresh air for me, since I've gotten used to the standard triple A level of charachter creation.Next up, the mechanics:The mechanics are fine, great even. Mechanics are introduced and reused. The mechanics are varied and work as they should. And there's one more thing, a very big and important thing. Gameplay work together with the ""story"". Seriously, this game does things better than most triple A's out there.And lastly, design:The levels are good enough. For me at least. I haven't got that much experience with puzzle platformers so I was surprised at the difficulty of this game. Other won't have this problem, because they have superbrains or something. The difficulty ramps up to almost at the end, but it never overstays it welcom by presenting levels that look very much alike over and over again. It is really short because of this, which is a shame, but I can't hate it for that little flaw.In conclusion. Some people might like it for the message, some for the mechanics and some for the challenge. In my opinion is the design not something which will hold it up, but it did help me in the decision making.I hope you do buy this lovely little game and have fun."
