76561198028617903,Recommended,305920,11963655,"Posted: 2 September, 2014",all,Nibbles,"Another Perspective is a quick, fun puzzle platformer with interesting game mechanics.  While on the short side (I completed the whole thing in less than 4 hours), its simple, well-designed structure makes it fun to play.  The levels tend to range from easy to moderate difficulty, which keeps things interesting without getting frustrating.  There are only a few difficult levels, including one that actually requires taking advantage of a 'glitch' in the game mechanics, showing some extra creativity on the designer's part.The Steam achievements are appropriate and keep the player looking for a few rewarding easter eggs within the game.  It also has an amusing ""story"" intended to make a player think, but not too hard.  It is obviously a game someone took pride in creating, and I would recommend this to any puzzle game enthusiast from beginner to expert, especially if it is on sale."
